Johannesburg The South African Revenue Service (Sars) customs officials have arrested a Bolivian man who was found in possession of over five kilograms of cocaine at OR Tambo International Airport.In a statement on Tuesday, Sars said the passenger was arrested on Sunday after 5.34 kg of cocaine with an estimated value of R1 536 318, was discovered. &quot;The passenger was passing through OR Tambo International to Lusaka when the drugs was found in a false compartment in the bottom and sides of his checked in bag.&quot; The suspect was handed over to police for further investigation. African News Agency